# Agent Instructions

This file provides instructions for GSD-2 and other AI coding agents.
For GitHub Copilot instructions, see `.github/copilot-instructions.md`.
For full agent documentation, see `AGENTS.md`.

## Quick Reference

### Architecture

Clean Architecture — Dependency Rule is the fundamental invariant.
Dependencies always point inward: `presentation/infrastructure → application → core`.

### Key Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `task dev` | Start development servers |
| `task test` | Run all tests |
| `task lint` | Run all linters |
| `task format` | Format all code |
| `task typecheck` | Type checking |
| `task registry:generate` | Regenerate constants from naming registry |

### Rules

- Read `AGENTS.md` for full project conventions
- Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for coding standards
- Follow Clean Architecture boundaries
- For frontend work, prefer shadcn/ui + React Router + React Hook Form + Vite + strict TypeScript patterns
- For frontend work, consult official shadcn/ui, React Router, and React Hook Form docs before implementation
- Use Context7, shadcn MCP, or official upstream docs for frontend reference lookups
- Use `task` commands (not raw pytest/ruff/etc.)
- Never use `print()` — use structured logging
- Never hardcode constants — use naming registry